the delta from the target wakeup time for 30 seconds. When the leap second triggers, on affected machines you'll see the output streams quickly, with negative diff values, as clock_nanosleep is immediately returning. To build: gcc leaptest-timer.c -o leaptest-timer -lrt I've reproduced this behaviour in kernel versions:
     v3.5-rc4
     v2.6.37
     v2.6.32.59
(And quite likely all in-between). I haven't been able to build or boot anything earlier with the distro on 
my current test boxes, but I'm working to get older distro installed so 
I can do further testing. Likely has potentially been around 
since:746976a301ac9c9aa10d7d42454f8d6cdad8ff2b in v2.6.22, as Ben Blum 
and Jan Ceuleers already noted. With my fix to call clock_was_set when we apply a leapsecond, I no 
longer see the issue. /* Leap second timer test
 *              by: john stultz (johnstul@us.ibm.com)
